rComments: Pretty decent lecturer, tries to make class more engaging. He's super specific about wording and it results in students sacrificing understanding for straight memorization because you have to replicate exactly what he says for him to consider it "proper communication". Even if you think you understand a concept you can still do really poorly
Alright teacher. He was very rude during personal interactions however... he should take GMN101 (Good Manners 101) again.

DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS (take it in french). He is a good lecturer but doesn't know how to correct midterm. You need to memorize EXACTLY word by word his definitions or you don't get full marks. Even then, the TAs take off marks just because. Material is easy, he just makes it so complicated. DO NOT RECOMMEND AT ALL.

He is an amazing professor. Clear, organized, helpful. His notes are well-made and give you all the information necessary to prepare the exam, he gives the tutorial himself. You have to study hard however the midterms are straightforward.

Provides a lot of chances to improve marks with a nicely divided marking scheme, tests are straightforward. Also gives helpful study questions, and runs the DGDs himself instead of foisting it off on a TA.

Protein structure is not exactly exciting material, but Baezinger does the best job I can imagine with it. He takes  a very different approach to teaching and gives assignments and quizzes that force students to ACTUALLY LEARN AND UNDERSTAND, rather than just uselessly memorizing crap from a textbook. His style should be adopted by all profs.
He's so straightforward and the midterms are fair. Study hard, this is not as simple as it looks.
